= content_for(:page_title) do
  Migrating to the Icon Engine

- # Token forms for the live rendering table: the token and what it shows.
- # Every token here is vendored in the demo's own icon set, so the third
- # column renders each icon live through the engine it documents.
- tokens = []
- tokens << ["bolt", "Just a name — the default library and variant"]
- tokens << ["bolt/solid", "A variant of the default library"]
- tokens << ["lucide:heart", "A different library"]
- tokens << ["phosphor:heart/duotone", "Library and variant together"]

.max-w-prose
  = doc_info(url: "https://github.com/Rails-Designer/icons", icon: "sparkles", icon_css: "text-primary") do
    :markdown
      _Loco_**Motion** now renders every icon through a small, pluggable
      **icon engine** built on the [`icons`](https://github.com/Rails-Designer/icons)
      gem — so you can use Heroicons, Lucide, Phosphor, and more from one API.

.prose
  :markdown
    # Migrating to the Icon Engine

    Earlier versions of LocoMotion depended on `rails_heroicon`, which shipped
    the entire Heroicons set inside the gem and exposed a `hero_icon` helper.
    That has been replaced by the `loco_icon` engine: LocoMotion bundles only
    a tiny set of icons and resolves everything else from the icons you **sync
    into your own app** — the same way [Tailwind](https://tailwindcss.com) only
    ships the CSS you actually use.

    This guide covers everything you need to change. Most apps only touch two
    things: run one sync command, and rename `hero_icon` to `loco_icon`.

- # The roadmap: migration steps with anchor links. The links opt out of
- # Turbo because the layout wraps pages in a turbo-frame, which would
- # otherwise swallow same-page anchor jumps.
.mt-8.rounded-box.border.border-base-300.p-6
  = daisy_steps(css: "w-full steps-vertical sm:steps-horizontal") do |steps|
    - steps.with_step(css: "step-primary") do
      %a{ href: "#sync", class: "link-hover", data: { turbo: "false" } } Sync icons
    - steps.with_step(css: "step-primary") do
      %a{ href: "#rename", class: "link-hover", data: { turbo: "false" } } Rename calls
    - steps.with_step(css: "step-primary") do
      %a{ href: "#replace", class: "link-hover", data: { turbo: "false" } } Replace the class
    - steps.with_step(css: "step-primary") do
      %a{ href: "#options", class: "link-hover", data: { turbo: "false" } } Icon options
    - steps.with_step(css: "step-primary") do
      %a{ href: "#tokens", class: "link-hover", data: { turbo: "false" } } Learn tokens
    - steps.with_step(title: "Ship it 🎉")

.mt-12.prose
  %h2{ id: "sync", class: "flex flex-col items-start gap-2 scroll-mt-24" }
    = daisy_badge("One-time", css: "badge-info badge-soft")
    %span 1. Sync your icons
  :markdown
    LocoMotion bundles just the handful of icons its own components need
    (`check`, `x-mark`, `trash`, and the calendar chevrons). Everything else —
    including most of Heroicons — now lives in your app. Sync the full
    Heroicons set once and commit the SVGs:

.max-w-prose
  = daisy_code(css: "my-4", prefix: "$") do
    bin/rails loco_motion:icons:add heroicons

.mt-4.prose
  :markdown
    Prefer to ship only what you use? Run the treeshaking sync instead — it
    scans your app (and a configurable safelist) and vendors only the icons
    you reference:

.max-w-prose
  = daisy_code(css: "my-4", prefix: "$") do
    bin/rails loco_motion:icons:sync

.mt-4.prose
  :markdown
    Both commands give each library its own folder —
    `app/assets/svg/icons/<library>/<variant>/` (e.g.
    `app/assets/svg/icons/heroicons/outline/`). Commit the SVGs; they render as
    inline `<svg>` with no runtime dependency on any gem.

.mt-12.prose
  %h2{ id: "rename", class: "flex flex-col items-start gap-2 scroll-mt-24" }
    = daisy_badge("Breaking", css: "badge-error badge-soft")
    %span
      2. Replace
      %code hero_icon
      with
      %code loco_icon
  :markdown
    The `hero_icon` helper (and the `heroicon` alias) have been removed. Rename
    calls to `loco_icon`:

.mt-6
  %div{ class: "grid grid-cols-1 gap-4 lg:grid-cols-2" }
    %div
      = daisy_badge("Before", css: "badge-ghost mb-2")
      = doc_code(language: "haml") do
        :plain
          = hero_icon("academic-cap")
    %div
      = daisy_badge("After", css: "badge-primary mb-2")
      = doc_code(language: "haml") do
        :plain
          = loco_icon("academic-cap")

.mt-4.prose
  :markdown
    If a call specified a variant or library, fold it into the icon name as a
    **token** rather than a separate option:
    `hero_icon("bolt", variant: :solid)` becomes `loco_icon("bolt/solid")`.
    See step 5 for the full token format (it's also what the sync scans).

.mt-12.prose
  %h2{ id: "replace", class: "flex flex-col items-start gap-2 scroll-mt-24" }
    = daisy_badge("Breaking", css: "badge-error badge-soft")
    %span
      3. Replace
      %code Hero::IconComponent
  :markdown
    The `Hero::IconComponent` wrapper has also been removed. Anywhere you
    rendered it directly, use the `loco_icon` helper instead:

.mt-6
  %div{ class: "grid grid-cols-1 gap-4 lg:grid-cols-2" }
    %div
      = daisy_badge("Before", css: "badge-ghost mb-2")
      = doc_code(language: "haml") do
        :plain
          = render(Hero::IconComponent.new(icon: "star"))
    %div
      = daisy_badge("After", css: "badge-primary mb-2")
      = doc_code(language: "haml") do
        :plain
          = loco_icon("star")

.mt-12.prose
  %h2{ id: "options", class: "flex flex-col items-start gap-2 scroll-mt-24" }
    = daisy_badge("Check usage", css: "badge-warning badge-soft")
    %span 4. Component icon options
  :markdown
    Options like `icon:`, `left_icon:`, `right_icon:`, and the Timeline event's
    `middle_icon:` now resolve through the same engine. They work with **no
    setup for the bundled icons** (LocoMotion's chrome plus the standard alert
    icons), but any other name — like `shopping-cart` — must be synced first
    (see step 1):

.max-w-prose
  = doc_code(css: "my-4", language: "haml") do
    :plain
      = daisy_alert(icon: "information-circle")      -# bundled, no sync
      = daisy_button("Cart", icon: "shopping-cart")  -# needs a sync

.mt-12.prose
  %h2{ id: "tokens", class: "flex flex-col items-start gap-2 scroll-mt-24" }
    = daisy_badge("Reference", css: "badge-neutral badge-soft")
    %span 5. Libraries and variants
  :markdown
    Specify a library or variant with a **token** — one string in the form
    `library:name/variant`, the same way [Iconify](https://iconify.design)
    names icons. The treeshaking sync scans your source for these strings, so
    keeping the library and variant *in the token* (rather than in separate
    options) is what lets `loco_motion:icons:sync` find and vendor the exact
    icons you use:

- # The token grammar as a table, with each token rendered live by the very
- # engine this guide documents.
.mt-4.overflow-x-auto.rounded-box.border.border-base-300
  = daisy_table(css: "table-zebra") do |table|
    - table.with_head do |head|
      - head.with_column { "Token" }
      - head.with_column { "Meaning" }
      - head.with_column { "Renders" }
    - tokens.each do |token, meaning|
      - table.with_row do |row|
        - row.with_column do
          %code= token
        - row.with_column do
          = meaning
        - row.with_column do
          = loco_icon(token, css: "size-6")

.mt-4.prose
  :markdown
    Add more libraries the same way you added Heroicons — run
    `bin/rails loco_motion:icons:list` to see the options.

.mt-12.prose
  %h2{ class: "scroll-mt-24" } Migration checklist

.max-w-prose.mt-6.flex.flex-col.gap-4{ class: "[&_.label]:items-start [&_.label]:whitespace-normal [&_code]:wrap-anywhere" }
  = daisy_checkbox(name: "icons_sync", id: "icons_sync") do |checkbox|
    - checkbox.with_trailing do
      :markdown
        Run `loco_motion:icons:add heroicons` (or `:sync`) once and commit
        the SVGs.
  = daisy_checkbox(name: "icons_rename", id: "icons_rename") do |checkbox|
    - checkbox.with_trailing do
      :markdown
        Rename `hero_icon` / `heroicon` calls to `loco_icon`.
  = daisy_checkbox(name: "icons_component", id: "icons_component") do |checkbox|
    - checkbox.with_trailing do
      :markdown
        Replace `Hero::IconComponent` with `loco_icon`.
  = daisy_checkbox(name: "icons_options", id: "icons_options") do |checkbox|
    - checkbox.with_trailing do
      :markdown
        Sync any icon a component references that isn't in the bundled set.

= daisy_divider

= doc_buttons(css: "mt-8", current_id: params[:id], section: "docs")
